<p>In a new digression – CORROSION – Stewart Brand writes on rust, a constant nemesis in the battle to maintain:</p><blockquote><p>DEFEATING RUST is an endless drudgery of oiling, greasing, brushing, scraping, cleansing, swabbing, painting, repainting, re-repainting, and finally discarding.  All that hassle and expense is a strong incentive to devote a great deal of science and engineering to improve the situation.  Thus maintenance issues are the force behind the anti-corrosion part of technological progress.  We want to make rust just go away, and it just won’t.  So we negotiate.</p></blockquote><p>Read the piece <a href="https://books.worksinprogress.co/book/maintenance-of-everything/vehicles/digression-3-corrosion-rust-never-sleeps/3" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">here</a>. Collaborate <a href="https://books.worksinprogress.co/book/maintenance-of-everything/vehicles/digression-3-corrosion-rust-never-sleeps/3?mode=suggest" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">here</a>.</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F99086d44-6a6a-4126-bcf6-19f58be13d3c_6000x4000.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ls4uYcSdW-hxJXEdZj-5tY45DAXVMx_PsWDBYhl33qU=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY5OTA4NmQ0NC02YTZhLTQxMjYtYmNmNi0xOWY1OGJlMTNkM2NfNjAwMHg0MDAwLmpwZWc= 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/AwRykClZA_ptN3GLE60TLnnn1F5MBGM8ycembUR_MVY=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N